  "title": "Research Engineer/Senior Research Engineer (Photonics) (NSTIC), IME",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job  Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop, design, and optimize  integration flow for Silicon Nitride-based and Lithium Niobate-based photonic  devices, including lithography, etching, deep-trench, and  dicing.</li>\n  <li>Design of experiments (DOE) for different  process integration flows.</li>\n  <li>Liaise between design, fabrication, and  testing teams to ensure smooth process integration and device fabrication.</li>\n  <li>Metrology, data analysis, and  documentation.</li>\n  <li>Present and discuss experimental data to  the team.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Qualifications:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Electronics Engineering,  Microelectronics, Physics, or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Experiences in semiconductor industry,  preferably in silicon photonic processes.</li>\n  <li>Good critical thinking and  problem-solving ability.</li>\n  <li>Able to work with cross-functional team,  with good communication/presentation skill.</li>\n  <li>Able to work in a fast-paced and  collaborative environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The above eligibility criteria are not exhaustive. A*STAR may include additional selection criteria based on its prevailing recruitment policies. These policies may be amended from time to time without notice. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></p>",
